<li>Cutshaw, Charlie; Shilin, Valery. <i>Legends and Reality of the AK: A Behind-the-Scenes Look at the History, Design, and Impact of the Kalashnikov Family of Weapons</i>. Boulder, CO: Paladin Press, 2000 (paperback, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1581600690" class="internal">ISBN 1-58160-069-0</a>).</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFEzell1986">Ezell, Edward Clinton (1986). <i>The AK-47 Story: Evolution of the Kalashnikov Weapons</i>. Mechanicsburg, PA: Stackpole Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0811709167" class="internal">ISBN 0-8117-0916-7</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+AK-47+Story%3A+Evolution+of+the+Kalashnikov+Weapons&amp;rft.aulast=Ezell&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+Clinton&amp;rft.au=Ezell%2C+Edward+Clinton&amp;rft.date=1986&amp;rft.place=Mechanicsburg%2C+PA&amp;rft.pub=Stackpole+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0-8117-0916-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:AK-47"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Before his death, Ezell was the curator of military history at the <a href="/wiki/Smithsonian_Museum" title="Smithsonian Museum" class="mw-redirect">Smithsonian Museum</a>.)</li>
